    "malilib.config.experimental.comment.sortExtensionModOptions": "設定画面に表示される設定項目を表示名順に並べ替える．\n\nこの処理は，基本MODの設定リストの末尾に\n拡張MODの設定が付加された後で実行される．\n基本MODの設定がデフォルトで辞書順に\nなっていない場合には，それらも並べ替えられる．\n\nこのオプションは，拡張MODによって\n追加される設定がある場合にのみ有効．\n基本MODの設定を強制的に並べ替える\n§e名前順で設定を並べ替え§rオプションも参照のこと．",
    "malilib.config.experimental.name.activeConfigProfile": "有効な設定プロファイル",
    "malilib.config.experimental.name.sortConfigsByName": "名前順で設定を並べ替え",
    "malilib.config.experimental.name.sortExtensionModOptions": "拡張MODの設定を並べ替え",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.actionbarHudTicks": "メッセージがアクションバーに表示されるtick時間",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.configWriteMethod": "The write \"method\" that is used for writing to the config files.\n\n- §aNormal Write§r - malilib writes to the config file directly\n- §aTemp and Rename§r - malilib writes to a temporary file first, and then renames the temporary file over the old file\n\n§aNormal Write§r should work if you want to symlink or hard link the config files from some other location, whereas §aTemp and Rename§r in that case would just replace the <st>symlink</st> or hardlinked file and thus \"break the link\".\n\n§aTemp and Rename§r on the other hand should be safer against config file corruption, if the game were to crash while the configs are being written to. But then again malilib now by default keeps backups of the config files anyway.\n\n§dNote:§r This option is actually redundant for symlinks, as symlinks currently always use direct writing instead of temporary files and renaming. This is only needed if you use hardlinked config files.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.enableActionbarMessages": "アクションバーに情報を表示するかどうか．\n録画や配信の際に役立つ場合がある．\nSakuraの「Streamer Mode」に着想を得たオプション．",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.enableConfigSwitcher": "右上に「設定切り替えメニュー」を表示して\n登録済みの設定画面を素早く切り替える.\n注意: 設定画面が登録されいない場合，\n自動的に登録を試みる．",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.enableLargeBarrelPreview": "Enable §dlargeBarrel§r Inventory Preview handling\nfor the Carpet-TIS §dlargeBarrel§r Carpet rule.\n§6NOTE: This does not check for the presence\n§6of Carpet-TIS, nor if the rule is enabled.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.enableStatusEffectsShift": "Enable the shifting of text lines rendering on the\nTOP_RIGHT while Status Effects are active.\nIf this is disabled, status effects may\ncover up the text at the top right.\nThis is meant for special cases when various\nGUI or Inventory mods modify the location\nof the vanilla Status Effects.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.ignoredKeys": "ここに設定したキーは完全に無視される",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.inGameMessageTimeout": "The time in seconds that an in game message should appear for.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.keyboardType": "Change your Keyboard Layout to an AZERTY-compatible keybind pattern.\nThis should help solve your '§eM§r' mapping to a '§eCOMMA§r', for ex.\n§6NOTE: Changing this setting could alter your saved keybinds;\n§6please check them all after adjusting this config.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.openGuiConfigs": "MaLiLibのゲーム内設定画面を開く",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.realmsCommonConfig": "すべてのRealmsサーバに対して\n共通の設定ファイル名を使用するかどうか．\n無効にした場合，サーバのIPアドレスとポートを\n名前に含む設定ファイルが生成される．\nただし，Realmsサーバのアドレスは定期的に変更されるため，\n設定名も頻繁に変更され，設定が正しく保存されない可能性がある．\n基本的に，一つのRealmsサーバのみで\nプレイする場合は有効のままにする．\n複数のRealmsサーバでプレイする場合には\n設定が混在する可能性がある．",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.renderTransparencyFix": "Disable the Vanilla §bImproved Transparency§r Experimental Video option.\nThis Video setting causes MaLiLib's rendering to be\nrendered behind water, and other things.\nDisable this if you want MaLiLib to\nignore if this configuration is enabled.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.translationLanguage": "Set the i18n language of MaLiLib independently of\nMinecraft's Language setting.\nThis option requires §btranslationOverrides§r to be enabled.\n§6NOTE: Changing this only will take effect after you\n§6close and re-open the config screen.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.translationMode": "Configure the Translation 'Mode' to be used.\nFollow Vanilla, Follow MaLiLib, Independent, or OFF.",
    "malilib.config.generic.comment.translationOverrides": "Enable MaLiLib's Translation Overrides system.\nThis system can replace the Vanilla translation system,\nand allow it to be configurable for each mod.",
